# Repository Structure

**Project**: LLM Engineering in Practice

> **📖 Single Source of Truth**: For the complete and detailed repository structure, naming conventions, and workflow standards, please refer to [README.md](../../README.md) and [docs/learning-plan.md](../../docs/learning-plan.md).

---

## Directory Expectations

| Folder       | Purpose                                               |
| ------------ | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| `prompts/`   | Prompt templates + metadata (JSON/YAML)               |
| `rag/`       | Index builders, retrievers, query pipelines           |
| `agents/`    | Agent loops, reasoning traces, tool registries        |
| `tools/`     | Tool / function call schema definitions               |
| `eval/`      | Metrics calculators, experiment logs, harness scripts |
| `scripts/`   | CLI utilities (ingest, batch eval, cost reporting)    |
| `notebooks/` | Exploratory analysis & prototyping                    |
| `docs/`      | Decision logs, retrospectives, learning plan          |
| `data/`      | Sample corpora / synthetic sets (non-sensitive)      |
| `src/`       | Source code modules (when needed)                     |
| `source-material/` | Staging area for raw content (Read-Only, never modify/delete) |

**Note**: If a folder is missing, create it with a minimal README or `.gitkeep` when first needed.

---

## Folder Intent

- **`prompts/`**: Prompt templates with metadata sidecars (`.prompt.txt` + `.meta.json`)
- **`rag/`**: Retrieval prototypes (index builders, query flows)
- **`agents/`**: Agent loops, reasoning traces, tool registries
- **`tools/`**: Custom tool / function call definitions
- **`eval/`**: Evaluation scripts, metrics, and experiment logging
- **`scripts/`**: Utility CLIs (ingest, batch eval, cost reporting)
- **`notebooks/`**: Exploratory Jupyter notebooks & analysis
- **`docs/`**: Documentation, guides, decision logs, weekly learning plans
- **`data/raw/`**: Unprocessed source data
- **`data/processed/`**: Cleaned / chunked / vectorizable data
- **`src/`**: Reusable source code modules
- **`source-material/`**: Staging area for raw content (Read-Only, never modify/delete)
